conditions.name: Admission Rescheduling Condition
conditions.description: Condition for rescheduling admission to the CRU.
conditions.text: Admission can be rescheduled if PG level is not 90 to 250 mg/dL on Day 1.

conditions.name: Stop Insulin Infusion Condition
conditions.description: Condition to stop the insulin infusion used to induce hypoglycemia.
conditions.text: Insulin infusion is stopped once bedside PG is <60 mg/dL.

conditions.name: Interim Safety Review Trigger
conditions.description: A safety review is conducted after the first 6 patients complete Period 2.
conditions.text: Safety data will be reviewed after the first 6 patients (regardless of type of diabetes) are administered LY900018 in Period 2.

conditions.name: Continuation after Interim Safety Review
conditions.description: Condition to continue dosing after the interim safety review.
conditions.text: If no clinically significant safety findings for treatment or study procedure are noted, the remaining patients will be dosed.

conditions.name: TE ADA Positive Condition
conditions.description: Condition for entering additional follow-up for immunogenicity.
conditions.text: Patients with TE ADA at follow-up/ED will undergo additional follow-up.

conditions.name: End of Additional Follow-up Condition
conditions.description: Criteria to stop the additional follow-up for TE ADA.
conditions.text: Additional follow-up continues until the titer returns to baseline (ie, returns to within a single 2-fold dilution of the baseline titer) or until 1 year after the last dose of study treatment.

conditions.name: Patient Replacement Criteria
conditions.description: Criteria for replacing a discontinued patient.
conditions.text: If patients discontinue from the study before completion of both periods with evaluable primary outcome for any reason, the patient may be replaced.

transitionRules.name: Transition to Additional Follow-up
transitionRules.text: Patients with TE ADA at follow-up/ED will undergo additional follow-up.

transitionRules.name: Handling of Inadvertently Enrolled Patients
transitionRules.text: If the sponsor or investigator identifies a patient who did not meet enrollment criteria and was inadvertently enrolled, a discussion must occur to determine if the patient may continue in the study. Documented approval is required to continue.

scheduleTimelineExits.name: Enrollment in another clinical study
scheduleTimelineExits.description: Enrollment in any other clinical study involving an investigational product or enrollment in any other type of medical research judged not to be scientifically or medically compatible with this study.

scheduleTimelineExits.name: Medical, Safety, or Regulatory Reasons
scheduleTimelineExits.description: Participation in the study needs to be stopped for medical, safety, regulatory, or other reasons consistent with applicable laws, regulations, and good clinical practice.

scheduleTimelineExits.name: Investigator Decision
scheduleTimelineExits.description: The investigator decides that the patient should be discontinued from the study for any reason.

scheduleTimelineExits.name: Patient Decision
scheduleTimelineExits.description: The patient, or legal representative, requests to be withdrawn from the study.

scheduleTimelineExits.name: Study Discontinuation for Safety
scheduleTimelineExits.description: Following the review of the safety data from the first 6 patients to complete Period 2 Day 1, the study will be stopped if deemed necessary for patient safety in the opinion of the Investigator and sponsor.

scheduleTimelineExits.name: Lost to Follow-up
scheduleTimelineExits.description: A patient will be considered lost to follow-up if he or she repeatedly fails to return for scheduled visits and is unable to be contacted by the study site.

scheduleTimelineExits.name: Study Completion
scheduleTimelineExits.description: Completion of all protocol-required visits, including the final follow-up visit.

scheduledDecisionInstances.name: Interim Safety Review Decision
scheduledDecisionInstances.timepointId: After first 6 patients complete Period 2 Day 1
scheduledDecisionInstances.description: Decision point to continue dosing remaining patients or stop the entire study based on safety data from the first 6 patients.

scheduledDecisionInstances.name: Admission Rescheduling Decision
scheduledDecisionInstances.description: Decision to proceed with or reschedule admission based on patient's plasma glucose level.

scheduledDecisionInstances.name: Additional Follow-up Decision
scheduledDecisionInstances.description: Decision to place a patient into an additional follow-up period for immunogenicity monitoring based on TE ADA status.
